audiod: audiod (elogind-driven audio session manager)
audiod:
audiod: A small system daemon that reacts to elogind's login1 user-lifecycle
audiod: signals (UserNew/UserRemoved) and manages the per-user PipeWire stack:
audiod: ordered start with a readiness gate on first login, targeted teardown
audiod: on last logout. It is the "systemd --user for audio" that Slackware
audiod: lacks, built from elogind + libslack daemon + shell. No systemd, no
audiod: dinit; elogind is used unmodified. Ships audioctl for user control.
audiod:
audiod: Requires: elogind. Respects the system PipeWire/PulseAudio switch.
